  "methodology": [
    "Traffic deaths and serious injuries come directly from the FHWA Transportation Performance Management dashboard by geography, using 2023 values and the latest prior year only where a 2023 serious-injury value is missing.",
    "Vehicle miles traveled are inferred from each geography's fatalities and fatality rate. That inferred mileage is then used with the 2023 national NHTSA injury-crash and property-damage-only crash rates to estimate lower-severity crash totals.",
    "Serious injury crashes are estimated from FHWA serious injuries using Washington's 2024 ratio of serious injuries to serious-injury crashes. The remaining injury crashes are split into possible-injury and minor-injury crashes using Washington's 2024 non-serious crash mix.",
    "Fatal-crash balls are estimated from traffic deaths using the 2023 national ratio of fatalities to fatal crashes. The death and serious-injury cards still show people, not crashes.",
    "The counterfactual applies an 88 percent reduction to no-injury crashes and a 92 percent reduction to injury crashes and fatal crashes, matching the simplified safety assumptions already used on this site."
  ]
}
